I'm sorry for any confusion, but it seems there has been a misunderstanding in the question. You mentioned that when you were six years old, your sister was half your age. However, later on, you stated that you are now eighty years old. This creates an apparent contradiction as if your sister is half of your current age (80), she would be 40 years old which contradicts the statement made at a younger age.

Could you please clarify or rephrase this question? I'm here to assist with any mathematical problems, not necessarily related to personal ages and relationships.
